snippet: Police officers loyal to the ousted leader Ali Abdullah Saleh stormed the Interior Ministry on Tuesday, setting off clashes in which at least 15 people were killed and 43 wounded.
abstract: Yemeni police officers loyal to ousted leader Ali Abdullah Saleh storm the Interior Ministry, setting off clashes in which at least 15 people are killed and 43 wounded; officers had been demonstrating outside the ministry, accusing the new government of corruption.
lead_paragraph: Police officers loyal to the ousted leader Ali Abdullah Saleh stormed the Interior Ministry on Tuesday, setting off clashes in which at least 15 people were killed and 43 wounded.
